Hungary May End Most Industry Taxes From 2013, Portfolio.hu Says

-- B y   Z o l t a n   S i m o n
-- 
2011-10-17T06:27:40Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-17/hungary-may-end-most-industry-taxes-from-2013-portfolio-hu-says.html
Hungary may no longer levy
extraordinary taxes on the energy, retail and telecommunication
industries after 2012 while halving a similar tax on the
financial industry, Portfolio.hu reported citing revenue
forecasts included in next yearâ€™s budget bill.  The government sees revenue from extraordinary levies on
the energy, retail and telecommunication industries falling to 1
billion forint ($4.7 million) in 2013 from 155 billion forint in
2012 and to zero from 2014, the financial news website said.
Revenue from the financial industry tax is forecast to drop to
90 billion forint from 2013, from 187 billion forint in 2012.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
